  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n<!--A clear and concise description of what the bug is and steps to reproduce it.-->\r\nWhen peer with connects with finalized epoch 0 (genesis epoch), we check it's root against\r\ngenesis block and throw error because finalized root should be ZERO_HASH and not hash of genesis block.\r\n\r\nNot sure how our sync tests passes with this error, I think we are creating status incorrectly because this returns wrong finalozed checkpoint in case of genesis:\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/master/packages/lodestar/src/chain/chain.ts#L90\r\n\r\nAccording to spec it should always be:\r\n`state.finalized_checkpoint.root for the state corresponding to the head block.`\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n<!--A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen.-->\r\nSkip finalized epoch verification if request epoch is GENESIS_EPOCH, fix status creation.\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\n<!--Steps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Go to '...'\r\n2. Click on '....'\r\n3. Scroll down to '....'\r\n4. See error\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\n<!--If applicable, add screenshots to help explain your problem.-->\r\n\r\n**Desktop (please complete the following information):**\r\n - OS: <!--[e.g. ubuntu, OSX High Siera]-->\r\n - Version: <!--[e.g. 22]-->\r\n - Branch: <!--[Master]-->\r\n - Commit hash: <!--[e8232]-->\r\n",
